New Records: Giannis Antetokounmpo's streak of 27 consecutive games with 20 or more points on at least 50% shooting from the field, the longest in NBA history, ended.
Key Match Events: Giannis Antetokounmpo recorded a triple-double with 11 points, 13 assists, and 12 rebounds.
Damian Lillard led the scoring effort for Milwaukee with 25 points, five rebounds, and three assists.
Bobby Portis contributed 20 points, seven rebounds, and three assists off the bench.
Milwaukee Bucks knocked down 22 three-pointers while shooting 50% from beyond the arc.
Milwaukee Bucks tallied 37 assists as a team.
Milwaukee Bucks held the Toronto Raptors to 45.1% shooting from the field.
Post-Match Reflections: Despite the end of Antetokounmpo’s scoring streak, Milwaukee's dominant win highlighted the team's depth and ability to perform collectively.
With Lillard finding his rhythm, Portis contributing off the bench, and the Bucks excelling from beyond the arc, they appear poised to continue their climb in the Eastern Conference.
